{
  "text": "The nonlocal correlation part of the vdW-DF-cx is the same as in the original Rutgers-Chalmers [CITATION_1] vdW-DF, which was derived from the fluctuation-dissipation theorem [CITATION_2] of electron gas for the description of the longrange vdW interaction [CITATION_3] . The method contains both the leading-order and higher-order contributions, the latter of which are important for solids [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] . Its exchange part is based on a modified semilocal functional, which aims to improve the short-range description.",
  "correct_citation": {
